20200324 ML Note¶

  • by using second hand car price prediction data as example.

Task1 Understanding¶

train.csv name - regDate - model - brand - bodyType - fuelType - gearbox - power - kilometer - notRepairedDamage - regionCode - seller - offerType - creatDate - price - v_0', 'v_1', 'v_2', 'v_3', 'v_4', 'v_5', 'v_6', 'v_7', 'v_8', 'v_9', 'v_10', 'v_11', 'v_12', 'v_13','v_14'embedding label encoding

Goal of competition: get a minimum MAE, between pred price and final test prize.

Task2 Explorary data analysis¶

EDA regular 'can-be-done' steps: 1. Importing data manipulation libs & data viz libs: pandas, numpy, scipy; matplotlib, seaborn 2. Importing datas: train data & test data - head(), shape() 3. General explorary: - Describe(), info() 4. NA value checking - Abnormal value checking 5. Realizing the distribution of predicted value - Checking the distribution - Checking skewness and kurtoisis - Checking the frequency of predicted value 6. Dividing features into categorical and numerical ones - Checking the "unique" distribution of categorical features unique 7. Numerical features analysis - Correlation analysis - Check some numerical features to get the skewness and kurtoisis - Viz of each numerical feature - Viz of relation between each 2 numerical features - Viz of relation between each multi numerical features 8. Categorical features analysis - Unique distribution unique - Viz of box plot from categorical features - Viz of violin graph from categorical features - Viz of bar chart from categorical features - Viz of frequency from each categorical features (count_plot) 9. Use pandas_profiling to output data report pandas_profiling

8.2. Viz of box plot from categorical features 类类别特征箱形图可视化¶

In [84]:
#  name regionCode
categorical_features = ['model',
 'brand',
 'bodyType',
 'fuelType',
 'gearbox',
 'notRepairedDamage']
for c in categorical_features:
    Train_data[c] = Train_data[c].astype('category')
    if Train_data[c].isnull().any():
        Train_data[c] = Train_data[c].cat.add_categories(['MISSING'])
        Train_data[c] = Train_data[c].fillna('MISSING')

def boxplot(x, y, **kwargs):
    sns.boxplot(x=x, y=y)
    x=plt.xticks(rotation=90)

f = pd.melt(Train_data, id_vars=['price'], value_vars=categorical_features)
g = sns.FacetGrid(f, col="variable",  col_wrap=2, sharex=False, sharey=False, size=5)
g = g.map(boxplot, "value", "price")
